Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "zahvaljujem" in different forms and positions, with translations in English:

1. Zahvaljujem *vam* na pomoći. (I thank *you* for your help.)
2. Hvala *vam*, ali to nije potrebno. (Thank *you*, but that's not necessary.)
3. Zahvaljujem *se* svima na podršci. (I thank *everyone* for their support.)
4. Zahvaljujem *mu* na pozivu. (I thank *him* for the invitation.)
5. Molim vas da zahvalite *gospođi* na ljubaznosti. (Please thank *the lady* for her kindness.)
6. Zahvaljujući *vama*, uspeo sam da završim projekat na vreme. (Thanks to *you*, I managed to finish the project on time.)
7. Ne znam kako da vam se *zahvalim* na ovome. (I don't know how to thank *you* for this.)
8. Zahvaljujući *ovome*, imaćemo više vremena za pripremu. (Thanks to *this*, we'll have more time to prepare.)
9. Zahvaljujem *se* na razumevanju. (I thank *you* for your understanding.)
10. Kolega mi se *zahvalio* za pomoć. (My colleague *thanked me* for the help.)

Note: In the examples above, the word "zahvaljujem" is used in different forms, including "zahvaljujem vam", "zahvaljujem se", "zahvaljujem mu", "zahvalite gospođi", "zahvaljujući vama", "zahvalim", and "zahvalio". The word is used in different positions within the sentence, such as at the beginning, middle, or end. The translations in English are provided in parentheses.